author: DENNIS WASZAK Jr.
title: No practice for Jets' Decker; Revis, Ivory limited
text:
No practice for Jets’ Decker; Revis, Ivory limited By DENNIS WASZAK Jr. - Associated Press   
FLORHAM PARK, N.J. (AP) - New York Jets wide receiver Eric Decker remains sidelined by a sprained left knee that could cause him to miss a second straight game. 
Decker was injured in Week 2 against Indianapolis and did not play against Philadelphia on Sunday. The Jets travel to London to play AFC East rival Miami this Sunday. 
Cornerback Darrelle Revis and running back Chris Ivory were limited Wednesday. Revis has a hamstring issue, but says he should be fine. Ivory is dealing with a strained quadriceps that kept him out against the Eagles although he was active. 
Right guard Willie Colon (sprained MCL) and wide receiver Chris Owusu (knee) are already out, and tight end Jeff Cumberland (concussion) and linebacker Trevor Reilly (finger infection) are unlikely to play.
